cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with object segmentation in video, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel and fast 3D filtering technique for finding the principal eigenvector of the graph's adjacency matrix, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with video processing, which could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
